# Ship accepted updates

When the user accepts or confirms a code change for this app (ngn-exchange), finish by shipping it unless they opt out in that turn.

1. **Repository root**: `ngn-exchange` (where `.git` lives).
2. **GitHub**: Stage only intentional files (never `.env`). Commit with a short, accurate message. Push to `origin` on `main` — remote is [EcoCycleIT/NGN-USDT](https://github.com/EcoCycleIT/NGN-USDT).
3. **Vercel**: From the same folder, run production deploy: `npx vercel --prod --yes` (project is linked under `ecocycleits-projects/ngn-exchange`).

If there is nothing to commit, still run deploy when the user asked to ship. If push or deploy fails, fix or report and retry when reasonable.
